content.text:
Let me analyze the images and provide a solution:

Main Target Image Analysis:
- Total blocks: 8 blocks (3 orange cylindrical, 3 red arch/triangular, 2 yellow rectangular)
- Layers: 3 layers
- Structure details:
  1. Base layer: Red arch blocks forming a curved base
  2. Middle layer: Yellow rectangular blocks spanning across red arch blocks
  3. Top layer: Orange cylindrical blocks
  4. A separate orange cylindrical structure on the left side

Block Dictionary Selection:
- Red arch blocks: Blocks 1 and 2
- Yellow rectangular blocks: Blocks 4, 5, and 6
- Orange cylindrical blocks: Blocks 7 and 8
- Orange triangular blocks: Blocks 11, 12, 13, 14, 15, 16

Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block 1 (red arch)
    Step2: Move block 1 (red arch) adjacent to first block
    Step3: Move block 4 (yellow rectangular) across red arch blocks
    Step4: Move block 5 (yellow rectangular) adjacent to first yellow block
    Step5: Move block 7 (orange cylindrical) on top of structure
    Step6: Move block 8 (orange cylindrical) adjacent to first cylindrical block
    Step7: Move block 11 (orange triangular) to complete top structure
}
